node.text: you graduated kindergarten and you didn’t quit. congratulations baby, you did it. you had ups and you had downs but you always found a way to turn it around. off to first grade you go. i want you to know i love watching you grow. mommys first man, you are a star. i know you’ll grow up to be the best man you already are. i don’t think first grade is ready for you. it’ll be something new that mommy will walk you all the way through. your intelligence, your honesty, your smart little humor. I’m not ready for all the little rumors. but i know you’re tough and a smart young man. mommy will always be your number one fan. I love you my sweet boy. kick first grades butt. @daimonantwonprincejr

node.text:
happy 2nd birthday to my wild child. when i found out i was pregnant with you my heart exploded with joy. IVF really worked! i couldnt believe i was having a little girl. someone i could go get my nails done with, someone to gang up on the boys with, to finally not be the only girl in the house, to love and to cherish for a lifetime. someone to call my best friend. when you entered this world i wanted to hide you forever, to protect you. i was scared.. but sharing your personality with the world is one of the best things i ever could’ve done. this world needs more people like you. you bring so much joy to everyone around you. always remember, NO MATTER WHAT you are BEAUTIFUL & I will tell you everyday until my very last breath. *im crying because my baby isn’t a baby anymore* 
mommy loves you sweet girl.
